### Digital Offices API - HTTP Requests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@accessToken = your-access-token-here
@refreshToken = your-refresh-token-here

### Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

### Login with credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword123",
  "rememberMe": true
}

### Google OAuth (ID token flow)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idToken": "google-id-token-from-frontend"
}

### Verify email address
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/email/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "verification-token-from-email"
}

### Request email verification (requires auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/email/request-verification
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Refresh access token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Example: Full registration flow
### 1. Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

### 2. Check email for verification token, then verify
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/email/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "verification-token-from-email"
}

